.pem vs .ppk?
>PEM(privacy Enhanced Mail) is downloaded from aws when you created your key-par for ec2 access.
>PPK(putty private key) is a windows ssh client, it does not support .pem format. 
>.pem files can be converted to .ppk using PuTTYgen.
>.pem is usually used in for AWS services, but if to be used for PuTTY or WinSCP .ppk file can be used.
>.ppk files are used to enable communication securely with another party having the corresponding public key.
>Systems platform compatibility: Linux (.pem), Mac (.pem), Windows PowerShell (.pem), Window PuTTY/Cygwin (.ppk)
